tab>\r\n<tabname><center>Support</center></tabname>\r\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc">\r\n</div>\r\n</tabtext>\r\n</newtab>\r\n\r\n<newtab>\r\n<tabname><center>More Images</center></tabname>\r\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc">\r\n</div>\r\n</tabtext>\r\n</newtab>', '', NULL, '', 1136, '<br><li>CT23BM03 - Double DIN Fascia</li>\r\n<li>CTSBM003 and CTSBM004 - Steering Control Interfaces With Wiring looms for Flat and round pin vehicles (saves having to guess what type you have) </li>\r\n<li>CT27AA06 - Antenna adaptor </li>', ''),
(1983, 1, 'JL Audio C2 CP112-W0v2 300W Single Slot-Ported Enclosure', '<newtab>\r\n<tabname><center>Description</center></tabname>\r\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc"><p>The JL Audio CP112-W0V2 potent slot-ported subwoofer system fits a wide variety of vehicles and extracts maximum performance from Jl Audio''s potent Wv2 subwoofer driver. Aggressive tuning delivers powerful bass without the need for a huge amplifier. (200-300 watts RMS is plenty). \r\n  \r\nThe clever enclosure design enables a variety of installation options: Forward, rear or down-firing! This allows the enclosure to be used in a wide variety of vehicles.</p><br>\r\n<p>BassWedge systems benefit from solid MDF construction and are finished in high-quality, dark gray carpet with attractive embroidered "JL AUDIO" and "Slot-Ported BassWedge" logos. Systems are wired, loaded and ready to connect to an amplifier via their nickel-plated push terminals. \r\n  \r\nReal JL Audio slot-ported performance has never been this affordable\r\n</div>\r\n</tabtext>\r\n</newtab>\r\n\r\n<newtab>\r\n<tabname><center>Features</center></tabname>\r\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc"><ul><li>Driver(s): One 12W0v2-4 </li>\r\n<li>Continuous Power Handling: 300W </li>\r\n<li>Final Impedance: 4 ohm mono  </li>\r\n<li>Enclosure Type: Slot-ported </li>\r\n<li>Finish: Dark gray carpet </li>\r\n<li>Net Weight: 33.1 lbs / 15 kg </li>\r\n<li>(H) Height  15.18 in. / 386 mm </li>\r\n<li>(W) Width 16.31 in. / 414 mm </li>\r\n<li>(D1) Depth 20.3 in. / 516 mm </li>\r\n<li>(D2) Top Surface Depth 15.74 in. / 400 mm </li></ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</tabtext>\r\n</newtab>\r\n\r\n<newtab>\r\n<tabname><center>Support</center></tabname>\r\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc">\r\n</div>\r\n</tabtext>\r\n</newtab>\r\n\r\n<newtab>\r\n<tabname><center>More Images</center></tabname>\r\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc">\r\n</div>\r\n</tabtext>\r\n</newtab>', '', NULL, '', 1903, '<br>\r\n<li>Driver(s): One 12W0v2-4 </li>\r\n<li>Continuous Power Handling: 300W </li>\r\n<li>Final Impedance: 4 ohm mono  </li>\r\n<li>Enclosure Type: Slot-ported </li>', ''),
(1984, 1, 'new JL Audio C2 CP112-W0v2 300W Dual Slot-Ported Enclosure', '<newtab>\r\n<tabname><center>Description</center></tabname>\r\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc"><p>The JL Audio CP212-W0V2 potent slot-ported dual chamber subwoofer enclosure system fits a wide variety of vehicles and extracts maximum performance from Jl Audio''s potent Wv2 subwoofer driver. Aggressive tuning delivers powerful bass without the need for a huge amplifier. (200-300 watts RMS is plenty).</p>  \r\n<center><img src="catalog/images/more images/19174.jpg"></center><br><br>\r\n<p>The clever enclosure design enables a variety of installation options: Forward, rear or down-firing! This allows the enclosure to be used in a wide variety of vehicles.</p><br>\r\n<p>BassWedge systems benefit from solid MDF construction and are finished in high-quality, dark gray carpet with attractive embroidered "JL AUDIO" and "Slot-Ported BassWedge" logos. Systems are wired, loaded and ready to connect to an amplifier via their nickel-plated push terminals. </p>\r\n<p>Real JL Audio slot-ported performance has never been this affordable!\r\n</div>\r\n</tabtext>\r\n</newtab>\r\n\r\n<newtab>\r\n<tabname><center>Features</center></tabname>\r\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc"><ul><li>Driver(s): Two 12W0v2-4 </li>\r\n<li>Continuous Power Handling: 600W </li>\r\n<li>Final Impedance: 2 ohm mono </li>\r\n<li>Enclosure Type: Slot-ported </li>\r\n<li>Finish: Dark gray carpet </li>\r\n<li>Net Weight: 60.3 lbs / 27.35 kg </li>\r\n<li>(H) Height  15.18 in. / 386 mm </li>\r\n<li>(W) Width 31.375 in. / 797 mm </li>\r\n<li>(D1) Depth 20.3 in. / 516 mm </li>\r\n<li>(D2) Top Surface Depth 15.75 in. / 400 mm </li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</tabtext>\r\n</newtab>\r\n\r\n<newtab>\r\n<tabname><center>Support</center></tabname>\r\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc">\r\n</div>\r\n</tabtext>\r\n</newtab>\r\n\r\n<newtab>\r\n<tabname><center>More Images</center></tabname>\r\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc">\r\n</div>\r\n</tabtext>\r\n</newtab>', '', NULL, '', 2161, '<br>\r\n<li>Driver(s): Two 12W0v2-4 </li>\r\n<li>Continuous Power Handling: 600W </li>\r\n<li>Final Impedance: 2 ohm mono </li>\r\n<li>Enclosure Type: Slot-ported </li>', ''),
(1985, 1, 'BMW 3 Series E93 Double Din Fascia Fitting Kit', '<newtab>\r\n<tabname><center>Description</center></tabname>\r\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc"><p>When replacing your factory fit radio with an aftermarket unit such as a Sony, Pioneer etc... You will probably require one of our specialist kits as the dash aperture will be a different size or shape.</p><br>\r\n<p>You will also find that the wiring connections will be different on most vehicles and we will supply you the harness to allow simple connection without the cutting of any cables leaving your warranty intact.</p><br>\r\n<p>Also some vehicles use a different aerial connection which we will also supply you in our full fitting kits.</p><br>\r\n<p>All the products we sell are from either Connects2, Autoleads or Celsus and of course are good quality and brand new.</p><br>\r\n<p>Whilst we endeavour to supply you with the correct lead with the descriptions we have no doubt there will be some vehicles caught in change over years so it would be useful when purchasing to match the picture with the type of fascia or loom of your vehicle prior to purchasing.</p><br>\r\n<p>This fitting kit includes:</p><br>\r\n<ul><li><a href="http://www.safensound.co.uk/connects2ct23bm01bmwdoubledinfaciaplatekit-p-1318.html" target="_blank">CT23BM01 BMW Double DIN Facia Plate Kit</a></li>\r\n<li><a href="http://www.safensound.co.uk/connects2bmwctsbm005steeringcontrollead-p-1132.html" target="_blank">BMW CTSBM005 Steering Control Lead</a></li>\r\n<li><a href="http://www.safensound.co.uk/connects2ct27aa16aerialadapter-p-1543.html" target="_blank">CT27AA16 Aerial Adapter</a></li>\r\n<li>CTRBM001 2 CAN-Bus Front & Rear Parking Alert Generator</li></ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</tabtext>\r\n</newtab>\r\n\r\n<newtab>\r\n<tabname><center>Features</center></tabname>\r\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc"><p><b>Suitable For:</b></p><br>\r\n<ul><li>BMW 3 Series E93</li></ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</tabtext>\r\n</newtab>\r\n\r\n<newtab>\r\n<tabname><center>Support</center></tabname>\r\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc">\r\n</div>\r\n</tabtext>\r\n</newtab>\r\n\r\n<newtab>\r\n<tabname><center>More Images</center></tabname>\r\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc">\r\n</div>\r\n</tabtext>\r\n</newtab>', '', NULL, '', 1615, '<br>\r\n<li>BMW 3 Series E93</li>', ''),
(624, 1, 'Vibe Blackair 69 v2 6X9 Car Speakers 525W', '<newtab>\r\n<tabname><center>Description</center></tabname>\r\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc"><p>The all new BlackAir speakers represent the pinnacle of in car entertainment speaker performance. The speaker is engineered such as to get perfect integration between the woofer and the tweeter. The woofer using a Honeycomb fibreglass cone combined with a polyurethane surround gives a sharp, precise and reference quality sound. The BlackAir range is an extremely musical speaker and unfailingly accurate in their performance.</p><br>\r\n<p>The silk dome tweeter is engineered such that it can keep up with and match the woofer perfectly and inherently with this has a very high power handling. The BlackAir range are capable of being mounted in component or coaxial form, making your installation choices incredibly versatile, the tweeter also comes with a multitude of installation choices including surface and flush mountings</p><br>\r\n<p>These speakers deliver reference quality sound helping you to produce razor sharp detail within your system. They provide exceptional sound delivered without any limitations. The BlackAir is the studio speaker designed for the car.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</tabtext>\r\n</newtab>\r\n\r\n<newtab>\r\n<tabname><center>Features</center></tabname>\r\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc"><ul><li>Vibe Blackair 69-V2 6"x9" car speakers</li>\r\n<li>Latest Version 2</li>\r\n<li>Peak Power 525w</li>\r\n<li>RMS Power 175w</li>\r\n<li>Freq Response 50Hz - 20kHz </li>\r\n<li>Mounting depth 93mm</li>\r\n<li>Machined front aluminium surround</li></ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</tabtext>\r\n</newtab>\r\n\r\n<newtab>\r\n<tabname><center>Support</center></tabname>\r\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc"><a href="" target="_blank"><img src="images/icons/pdf.png" align="left" style="vertical-align:middle"/>Instruction Manual</a><br>\r\n</div>\r\n</tabtext>\r\n</newtab>\r\n\r\n<newtab>\r\n<tabname><center>More Images</center></tabname>\r\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc"><p></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</tabtext>\r\n</newtab>', 'www.vibeaudio.co.uk/products/blackair69/', NULL, '', 510, '<br>\r\n<li>Latest Version 2</li>\r\n<li>Peak Power 525w</li>\r\n<li>RMS Power 175w</li>\r\n<li>Freq Response 50Hz - 20kHz </li>', ''),
(625, 1, 'Vibe LiteAir 5 5" Component System', '<newtab>\r\n<tabname><center>Description</center></tabname>\r\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc"><p>Building on the success of BlackAir, the Level 3 Vibe LiteAir range is designed for supercars, modified and performance tuned vehicles. Exceptional sound without adding excessive weight.</p><br>\r\n<p>The Vibe Lite Air Series have been developed with NEO magnets which are flat - giving the lowest possible mounting depths for simple fitment in almost any factory location.</p><br>\r\n<p>This 5" component system has an incredible 1.8" mounting depth.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</tabtext>\r\n</newtab>\r\n\r\n<newtab>\r\n<tabname><center>Features</center></tabname>\r\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc"><ul><li>Type: Component</li>\r\n<li>Configuration: 2 Way</li>\r\n<li>Speaker Size: 5.25" (133mm)</li>\r\n<li>RMS Power: 90 Watts</li>\r\n<li>Peak Power: 270 Watts</li>\r\n<li>Min. Input: 45W RMS</li>\r\n<li>Sensitivity: 90dB</li>\r\n<li>Freq Response: 60Hz - 25kHz</li>\r\n<li>Impedance: 4 Ohm</li>\r\n<li>Mounting Depth: 1.8" (45mm)</li>\r\n<li>Mounting Diameter: 4.7" (120mm)</li>\r\n<li>Voice Coil Diameter: 1" (25mm)</li>\r\n<li>Magnet Material: Neodymium</li>\r\n<li>Magnet Weight: 0.6oz</li>\r\n<li>Magnet Rating: N35</li></ul>\r\n</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</tabtext>\r\n</newtab>\r\n\r\n<newtab>\r\n<tabname><center>Support</center></tabname>\r\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc"><p></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</tabtext>\r\n</newtab>\r\n\r\n<newtab>\r\n<tabname><center>More Images</center></tabname>\r\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc"><p></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</tabtext>\r\n</newtab>', 'www.vibeaudio.co.uk/products/liteair5/', NULL, '', 389, '<br>\r\n<li>Type: Component</li>\r\n<li>Configuration: 2 Way</li>\r\n<li>Speaker Size: 5.25" (133mm)</li>\r\n<li>RMS Power: 90 Watts</li>', ''),
(626, 1, 'Vibe LiteAir 6 6.5" Component System', '<newtab>\r\n<tabname><center>Description</center></tabname>\r\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc"><p>Building on the success of BlackAir, the Level 3 Vibe LiteAir range is designed for supercars, modified and performance tuned vehicles. Exceptional sound without adding excessive weight.</p><br>\r\n<p>The Vibe Lite Air Series have been developed with NEO magnets which are flat - giving the lowest possible mounting depths for simple fitment in almost any factory location.</p><br>\r\n<p>This 6.5" component system has an incredible 1.8" mounting depth.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</tabtext>\r\n</newtab>\r\n\r\n<newtab>\r\n<tabname><center>Features</center></tabname>\r\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc"><ul><li>Type: Component</li>\r\n<li>Configuration: 2 Way</li>\r\n<li>Speaker Size: 6.5" (165mm)</li>\r\n<li>RMS Power: 100 Watts</li>\r\n<li>Peak Power: 300 Watts</li>\r\n<li>Min. Input: 50W RMS</li>\r\n<li>Sensitivity: 90dB</li>\r\n<li>Freq Response: 55Hz - 25kHz</li>\r\n<li>Impedance: 4 Ohm</li>\r\n<li>Mounting Depth: 1.8" (45mm)</li>\r\n<li>Mounting Diameter: 5.6" (143mm)</li>\r\n<li>Voice Coil Diameter: 1" (25mm)</li>\r\n<li>Magnet Material: Neodymium</li>\r\n<li>Magnet Weight: 0.6oz</li>\r\n<li>Magnet Rating: N35</li></ul>\r\n</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</tabtext>\r\n</newtab>\r\n\r\n<newtab>\r\n<tabname><center>Support</center></tabname>\r\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc"><p></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</tabtext>\r\n</newtab>\r\n\r\n<newtab>\r\n<tabname><center>More Images</center></tabname>\r\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc"><p></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</tabtext>\r\n</newtab>', 'www.vibeaudio.co.uk/products/liteair6/', NULL, '', 430, '<br>\r\n<li>Type: Component</li>\r\n<li>Configuration: 2 Way</li>\r\n<li>Speaker Size: 6.5" (165mm)</li>\r\n<li>RMS Power: 100 Watts</li>', ''),
(627, 1, 'Vibe Space 3D 13cm (5") 3-way component speakers', '<newtab>\r\n<tabname><center>Description</center></tabname>\r\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc"><p>Perfection is rare, almost everything can be improved upon - but with the Space 3D component speakers Vibe believe they have reached the pinnacle of in car audiophile sound. Designed with no compromise the Space 3D is a truly unique 3-way upgrade package which will push the boundaries of what you believed was possible. </p><br>\r\n<p>The 3D set includes a fantastic aluminium cone 45mm midrange driver with a silk dome Super Tweeter that delivers high frequencies with clarity and definition up to 35KHz.</p><br>\r\n<p>The unique feature of the Space speakers is the unique 3D mounting option - where the tweeter can be placed above the midrange making a regular 2-way setup - perfect for vehicles where mounting options are limited.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</tabtext>\r\n</newtab>\r\n\r\n<newtab>\r\n<tabname><center>Features</center></tabname>\r\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc"><ul><li>Configuration: mid/tweeter </li>\r\n<li>Speaker Size: 3" </li>\r\n<li>RMS Power: 70 w </li>\r\n<li>Peak Power: 210 w </li>\r\n<li>Sensitivity: 86 db </li>\r\n<li>Freq. Response: 25 - 35Khz </li>\r\n<li>Mounting Depth: 31mm </li>\r\n<li>Mounting Diameter: 57mm </li>\r\n<li>Voice coil diameter: 20mm </li>\r\n<li>Supplied with Grilles</li></ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</tabtext>\r\n</newtab>\r\n\r\n<newtab>\r\n<tabname><center>Support</center></tabname>\r\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc"><p></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</tabtext>\r\n</newtab>\r\n\r\n<newtab>\r\n<tabname><center>More Images</center></tabname>\r\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc"><p></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</tabtext>\r\n</newtab>', 'www.vibeaudio.co.uk/products/space3D/', NULL, '', 565, '<br>\r\n<li>Configuration: mid/tweeter </li>\r\n<li>Speaker Size: 3" </li>\r\n<li>RMS Power: 70 w </li>\r\n<li>Peak Power: 210 w </li>', ''),
(628, 1, 'Vibe Space 5 5.25" Speaker Component Kit', '<newtab>\r\n<tabname><center>Description</center></tabname>\r\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc"><p>Perfection is rare, almost everything can be improved upon - but with the VIBE Space 3D component speakers we believe we have reached the pinnacle of in car audiophile sound.\r\nDesigned with no compromise the Space 3D is a truly unique 3-way component speaker package which will push the boundaries of what you believed was possible.</p><br>\r\n<p>Featuring an ultra thin, yet extremely stiff 0.15mm thick aluminium cone which delivers audio with incredible dynamics and a dual layer progressive PU surround which allows increased bass delivery at low volumes while keeping tighter control of the woofer cone at high volumes. \r\nAvailable with either a five or a six inch main driver unit the set also includes a fantastic 45mm midrange driver which features the same cone material as the main unit. The Silk Dome Super Tweeter delivers high frequencies with clarity and definition up to 35KHz.</p><br>\r\n<p>The unique feature of the SPACE speakers is the unique 3D mounting option - where the tweeter can be placed above the midrange - perfect for vehicles where mounting options are limited. \r\nThe SPACE 3D is the last speaker you will ever need to purchase.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</tabtext>\r\n</newtab>\r\n\r\n<newtab>\r\n<tabname><center>Features</center></tabname>\r\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc"><ul><li>13cm (5.25") 3-way SPACE components</li>\r\n<li>RMS Power: 100w </li>\r\n<li>Peak Power: 300w </li>\r\n<li>Sensitivity: 90dB </li>\r\n<li>Frequency Response: 60 - 25,000Hz </li>\r\n<li>Impedance: 4ohm </li>\r\n<li>Mounting Depth: 55mm </li>\r\n<li>Mounting Diameter: 120mm</li>\r\n<li>Voice Coil Diameter: 35mm</li></ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</tabtext>\r\n</newtab>\r\n\r\n<newtab>\r\n<tabname><center>Support</center></tabname>\r\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc"><p></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</tabtext>\r\n</newtab>\r\n\r\n<newtab>\r\n<tabname><center>More Images</center></tabname>\r\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc"><p></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</tabtext>\r\n</newtab>', 'www.vibeaudio.co.uk/products/space5/', NULL, '', 465, '<br>\r\n<li>RMS Power: 100w </li>\r\n<li>Peak Power: 300w </li>\r\n<li>Sensitivity: 90dB </li>\r\n<li>Frequency Response: 60 - 25,000Hz </li>', ''),
(629, 1, 'Vibe Space 6 16.5cm Components Speakers', '<newtab>\r\n<tabname><center>Description</center></tabname>\r\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc"><p>Perfection is rare, almost everything can be improved upon - but with the VIBE Space 3D component speakers we believe we have reached the pinnacle of in car audiophile sound.</p><br>\r\n<p>Designed with no compromise the Space 3D is a truly unique 3-way component speaker package which will push the boundaries of what you believed was possible.</p><br>\r\n<p>Featuring an ultra thin, yet extremely stiff 0.15mm thick aluminium cone which delivers audio with incredible dynamics and a dual layer progressive PU surround which allows increased bass delivery at low volumes while keeping tighter control of the woofer cone at high volumes. </p><br>\r\n<p>Available with either a five or a six inch main driver unit the set also includes a fantastic 45mm midrange driver which features the same cone material as the main unit. The Silk Dome Super Tweeter delivers high frequencies with clarity and definition up to 35KHz.</p><br>\r\n<p>The unique feature of the SPACE speakers is the unique 3D mounting option - where the tweeter can be placed above the midrange - perfect for vehicles where mounting options are limited. \r\nThe SPACE 3D is the last speaker you will ever need to purchase.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</tabtext>\r\n</newtab>\r\n\r\n<newtab>\r\n<tabname><center>Features</center></tabname>\r\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc"><ul><li>16.5cm (6.5") 3-way SPACE components</li>\r\n<li>RMS Power: 120w </li>\r\n<li>Peak Power: 360w </li>\r\n<li>Sensitivity: 90dB </li>\r\n<li>Frequency Response: 55 - 25,000Hz </li>\r\n<li>Impedance: 4ohm </li>\r\n<li>Mounting Depth: 65mm </li>\r\n<li>Mounting Diameter: 143mm</li>\r\n<li>Voice Coil Diameter: 35mm</li></ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</tabtext>\r\n</newtab>\r\n\r\n<newtab>\r\n<tabname><center>Support</center></tabname>\r\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc"><p></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</tabtext>\r\n</newtab>\r\n\r\n<newtab>\r\n<tabname><center>More Images</center></tabname>\r\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc"><p></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</tabtext>\r\n</newtab>', 'www.vibeaudio.co.uk/products/space6/', NULL, '', 460, '<br>\r\n<li>RMS Power: 120w </li>\r\n<li>Peak Power: 360w </li>\r\n<li>Sensitivity: 90dB </li>\r\n<li>Frequency Response: 55 - 25,000Hz </li>', ''),
(630, 1, 'Vibe Deep Space 8"  4-Ohm Subwoofer', '<newtab>\n<tabname><center>Description</center></tabname>\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc"><p>The VIBE R&D masters proudly present the SPACE range of Performance SPL subwoofers. We use the term sound pressure level (SPL) lightly, because the SPACE woofer is as much a reference sub as it is an SPL sub - yet it still sits a class above most SPL subwoofers. We have achieved what most SPL subwoofers fail through continuous engineering combined with new technologies and materials  this has enabled us to create an immaculate subwoofer  producing reference sound quality at huge sound pressure levels. </p><br>\n<p>Making a subwoofer that can produce SPL levels of both tight bass and deep bass to a good musical level is near impossible  VIBE R&D have been researching this success for many years  we believe we have surpassed on our own goals and now offer it to you in the form of the SPACE subwoofer.\nTo summate; the SPACE has the dexterity of a light footed 8" sub and the power of a heavyweight competition SPL spec sub. This is undoubtedly the VIBE teams favourite product for all the reasons you are reading here. Perfection in low frequency reproduction.</p>\n</div>\n</tabtext>\n</newtab>\n\n<newtab>\n<tabname><center>Features</center></tabname>\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc"><ul><li>Woofer: 200mm (8")</li>\n<li>Impedance: 4-ohm</li>\n<li>Voice coil: 1.5" aluminium 2 layer</li>\n<li>Power Handling: 300 Watts RMS Power, 900W MAX Power</li>\n<li>Frequency response: 20 - 500Hz </li>\n<li>Sensitivity: 86dB</li>\n<li>Mounting depth: 114mm</li>\n<li>Mounting diameter: 185mm</li>\n<li>Magnet material: Ferrite</li>\n<li>Magnet weight: 34 Oz</li></ul>\n</div>\n</tabtext>\n</newtab>\n\n<newtab>\n<tabname><center>Support</center></tabname>\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc"><p></p>\n</div>\n</tabtext>\n</newtab>\n\n<newtab>\n<tabname><center>More Images</center></tabname>\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc"><p></p>\n</div>\n</tabtext>\n</newtab>', 'www.vibeaudio.co.uk/products/deepspace8/', NULL, '', 61, '<br>\n<li>Woofer: 200mm (8")</li>\n<li>Impedance: 4-ohm</li>\n<li>Voice coil: 1.5" aluminium 2 layer</li>\n<li>Frequency response: 20 - 500Hz </li>\n', ''),
(633, 1, 'Focal Access 130A1 Component Speakers', '<newtab>\n<tabname><center>Description</center></tabname>\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc"><p>Focal Access speakers create a natural musical soundstage. Focal builds, inspects, and tests every Access speaker to ensure that each one lives up to their high quality standards.</p><br>\n<p>The Access 130 A1 component speaker system features a 5" woofer with a stiff, woven glass fibre cone for precise bass and midrange reproduction. The strong, lightweight ABS frame offers plenty of open space for clean cone movement, along with excellent venting to cool the voice coils.</p><br>\n<p>The Access line''s defining reference combines high power handling, extended low frequency response, large soundstage, high dynamics and high efficiency. \n</p>\n</div>\n</tabtext>\n</newtab>\n\n<newtab>\n<tabname><center>Features</center></tabname>\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc"><ul><li>2-way 13cm (5.25") component speakers</li>\n<li>Woofer: 130mm</li>\n<li>Voice Coil: 25mm</li>\n<li>Magnet: 85mm</li>\n<li>TN 44, aluminum inverted dome tweeter</li>\n<li>Crossover: 12/12dB/octave (5kHz) with adjustable tweeter 3 level settings</li>\n<li>Max. power handling: 100W</li>\n<li>Nom. power handling: 50W</li>\n<li>Sensitivity: (2,83 V/1m) : 91dB</li>\n<li>Frequency response: 65Hz-20KHz</li>\n<li>Grilles supplied (woofer), flush mounting and surface mounting supports provided (tweeter)</li></ul>\n</div>\n</tabtext>\n</newtab>\n\n<newtab>\n<tabname><center>Support</center></tabname>\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc"><p></p>\n</div>\n</tabtext>\n</newtab>\n\n<newtab>\n<tabname><center>More Images</center></tabname>\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc"><p></p>\n</div>\n</tabtext>\n</newtab>', '', NULL, '', 192, '<li>TN 44, aluminum inverted dome tweeter</li>\n<li>Max. power handling: 100W</li>\n<li>Nom. power handling: 50W</li>\n', ''),
(634, 1, 'Focal K2 Power 165KR 16.5cm component speakers', '<newtab>\r\n<tabname><center>Description</center></tabname>\r\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc"><p><b>Focal K2 Power 165KR 16.5cm 2-way component speakers</b></p><br>\r\n<p>At Focal, all that matters is music. Focal''s sound gurus engage in intensive listening sessions as they design a new line of speakers, making it their mission to create products that deliver uncanny realism, sweeping dynamics, and breathtaking depth. During the hands-on production process, they test every model meticulously to ensure that they meet Focal''s exacting standards. </p><br>\r\n<p><b>Focal''s "Power Hi-Fi" philosophy</b></p><br>\r\n<p>The K2 Power 165KR 6-1/2" component speaker system bears the hallmarks of Focal''s "Power Hi-Fi" philosophy. The nimble Aramid and glass-fiber woofers demonstrate the control needed to reproduce delicate classical passages, yet they''ll handle the power needed to drive your bass-heavy music with authority. The sturdy zinc-aluminum alloy baskets are non-magnetic so they won''t interfere with the speaker''s own electronics. </p><br>\r\n<p><b>Inverted dome tweeter design</b></p><br>\r\n<p>Focal''s inverted dome tweeters act like little woofers, dispersing the highs in a wide pattern to create an exceptionally natural soundstage. K2 Power crossovers use hand-made components developed by Focal to deliver an ideal blend of the highs and lows for a dynamic stereo image. Three levels of tweeter and two levels of midrange control let you dial in the sound to your car''s environment. \r\n</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</tabtext>\r\n</newtab>\r\n\r\n<newtab>\r\n<tabname><center>Features</center></tabname>\r\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc"><ul><li>component speaker system includes two 6-1/2" woofers, 2 tweeters, 2 external crossovers, and 2 woofer grilles</li>\r\n<li>K2 composite woofer cone (Aramid, foam, and glass fiber)</li>\r\n<li>butyl rubber surround</li>\r\n<li>1-3/4" woven Aramid fiber inverted-dome tweeter</li>\r\n<li>2-way external crossover with 3 tweeter and 2 midrange level settings</li>\r\n<li>4-ohm impedance</li>\r\n<li>80 watts RMS (160 watts peak power)</li>\r\n<li>frequency response: 60-20,000 Hz</li>\r\n<li>sensitivity: 91 dB @ 2.83 V</li>\r\n<li>mounting depth: 2-13/16"</li></ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</tabtext>\r\n</newtab>\r\n\r\n<newtab>\r\n<tabname><center>Support</center></tabname>\r\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc"><p></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</tabtext>\r\n</newtab>\r\n\r\n<newtab>\r\n<tabname><center>More Images</center></tabname>\r\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc"><p></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</tabtext>\r\n</newtab>', '', NULL, '', 1434, '<li>butyl rubber surround</li>\r\n<li>1-3/4" woven Aramid fiber inverted-dome tweeter</li>\r\n<li>power range: 80 watts RMS (160 watts peak power)</li>', ''),
(635, 1, 'Vibe Slick 10 25cm (10inch) Subwoofer', '<newtab>\n<tabname><center>Description</center></tabname>\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc"><p>The SLICK subwoofer is a new breed of VIBE subwoofer. It features a single piece rubber surround and gasket which gives it a truly unique look especially when the same rubberised finish is applied to the single piece IMPP cone and the chassis. Vibes R&D team has been hard at work ensuring that the Slick subwoofers offer the ultimate in performance and technical advances such as dual progressive Conex spiders and multi layer, heavy gauge copper voice coil winding ensure that the performance of this subwoofer is class leading. Finishing touches such as the spring loaded, nickel plated speaker terminals and the rubber T-yoke with unique slick detailing show that nothing has been left to chance with these subwoofers. The characteristics of the Slick subwoofer are quite unique in that they produce overwhelming amounts of tight accurate bass, if its fast slamming bass you want, the Slick range of subwoofers are your perfect choice.\n</p>\n</div>\n</tabtext>\n</newtab>\n\n<newtab>\n<tabname><center>Features</center></tabname>\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc"><ul><li>RMS Power: 350w </li>\n<li>Peak Power: 1000w </li>\n<li>Sensitivity: 88dB </li>\n<li>Frequency Response: 20-1700hz </li>\n<li>Speaker Size: 10inch (255mm) </li>\n<li>Impedance: 4ohm </li>\n<li>Mounting Depth: 126mm </li>\n<li>Mounting Diameter: 232mm</li></ul>\n</p>\n</div>\n</tabtext>\n</newtab>\n\n<newtab>\n<tabname><center>Support</center></tabname>\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc"><a href="http://www.vibeaudio.co.uk/support/tsparameters/sub-slick10.pdf" target="_blank"><img src="images/icons/pdf.png" align="left" style="vertical-align:middle"/>Instruction Manual</a><br>\n</div>\n</tabtext>\n</newtab>\n\n<newtab>\n<tabname><center>More Images</center></tabname>\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc"><p></p>\n</div>\n</tabtext>\n</newtab>', 'www.vibeaudio.co.uk/products/slicksub10/', NULL, '', 49, '<br>\n<li>RMS Power: 350w </li>\n<li>Peak Power: 1000w </li>\n<li>Sensitivity: 88dB </li>\n<li>Frequency Response: 20-1700hz </li>\n', ''),
(636, 1, 'Vibe Slick 12 30cm (12inch) Subwoofer', '<newtab>\n<tabname><center>Description</center></tabname>\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc"><p>The SLICK subwoofer is a new breed of VIBE sub; it features a single piece rubber surround and gasket which gives it a truly unique look especially when the same rubberised finish is applied to the single piece IMPP cone and the chassis. VIBEs R&D team has been hard at work ensuring that the SLICK subwoofers offer the ultimate in performance and technical advances such as dual progressive Conex spiders and multi layer, heavy gauge copper voice coil winding ensure that the performance of this subwoofer is class leading.</p><br>\n<p>Finishing touches such as the spring loaded, nickel plated speaker terminals and the rubber T-yoke with unique slick detailing show that nothing has been left to chance with these subwoofers. The SLICK subwoofers also feature a unique one piece rubber gasket and surround, this not only creates a completely seamless look to the front of the woofer but as the gasket and surround are one piece there is no possibility of these two parts separating even under high power conditions.</p><br>\n<p>The characteristics of the SLICK sub are quite unique in that they produce overwhelming amounts of tight accurate bass, if its fast slamming bass you want, the SLICK range of subwoofers are your perfect choice.</p>\n</div>\n</tabtext>\n</newtab>\n\n<newtab>\n<tabname><center>Features</center></tabname>\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc"><ul><li>30cm (12inch) Subwoofer</li>\n<li>RMS Power: 400w Peak Power: 1200w</li>\n<li>Sensitivity: 90dB</li>\n<li>Frequency Response: 20-1500hz</li>\n<li>Impedance: 4ohm Mounting</li>\n<li>Depth: 133mm Mounting</li>\n<li>Diameter: 275mm</li></ul>\n</div>\n</tabtext>\n</newtab>\n\n<newtab>\n<tabname><center>Support</center></tabname>\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc"><a href="http://www.vibeaudio.co.uk/support/tsparameters/sub-slick12.pdf" target="_blank"><img src="images/icons/pdf.png" align="left" style="vertical-align:middle"/>Instruction Manual</a><br>\n</div>\n</tabtext>\n</newtab>\n\n<newtab>\n<tabname><center>More Images</center></tabname>\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc"><p></p>\n</div>\n</tabtext>\n</newtab>', 'www.vibeaudio.co.uk/products/slicksub12/', NULL, '', 51, '<br>\n<li>30cm (12inch) Subwoofer</li>\n<li>RMS Power: 400w Peak Power: 1200w</li>\n<li>Sensitivity: 90dB</li>\n<li>Frequency Response: 20-1500hz</li>\n', '');
