(641, 1, 'Vibe BlackAir BA15 v3 2000W 15" Subwoofer', '<newtab>\n<tabname><center>Description</center></tabname>\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc"><p>Bass is the rhythm of life and the new BlackAir subwoofer is the beat behind that rhythm. The eye catching subwoofer features a specially fabricated fibreglass composite cone which delivers bass with power and precision. The cone is partnered with a unique High Roll rubber edge surround which allows for exceptional excursion which is fully under control. </p><br>\n<p>The all new magnet is significantly larger resulting in gains in both sound quality and power while the rubber boot protects the magnet and integrates with the basket, while the VIBE Angular Torsion basket has five vented arms which cradle the cone and allow the coil to breathe cool air. </p><br>\n<p>The Alloy gasket signs off the BlackAir in true VIBE style - and is fully removable for the option of rear mounting. Add to all of this the fact that the BlackAir now comes with dual 2ohm voice coils and you have a subwoofer which not only looks fantastic but offers slamming bass even the most brutal of bass heads can appreciate.</p>\n</div>\n</tabtext>\n</newtab>\n\n<newtab>\n<tabname><center>Features</center></tabname>\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc"><ul><li>Speaker Size: 15" (392mm) </li>\n<li>RMS Power: 650W </li>\n<li>Peak Power: 2000W </li>\n<li>Minimum Input: 200W RMS </li>\n<li>Sensitivity: 90db </li>\n<li>Freq.Response: 20 - 850 Hz </li>\n<li>Mounting Depth: 190mm </li>\n<li>X-Max: 8mm </li>\n<li>Voice Coil: 2" aluminium 4 layer </li>\n<li>Magnet Material: Ferite </li>\n<li>Magnet Weight: 75oz </li>\n<li>Magnet Size: 170x 25mm </li>\n<li>Magnet Rating: Y25 </li></ul>\n</div>\n</tabtext>\n</newtab>\n\n<newtab>\n<tabname><center>Support</center></tabname>\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc"><a href="http://www.vibeaudio.co.uk/support/tsparameters/sub-blackair15.pdf" target="_blank"><img src="images/icons/pdf.png" align="left" style="vertical-align:middle"/>Instruction Manual</a><br>\n</div>\n</tabtext>\n</newtab>\n\n<newtab>\n<tabname><center>More Images</center></tabname>\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc"><p></p>\n</div>\n</tabtext>\n</newtab>', 'www.vibeaudio.co.uk/products/blackairsub15/', NULL, '', 71, '<br>\n<li>Speaker Size: 15" (392mm) </li>\n<li>RMS Power: 650W </li>\n<li>Peak Power: 2000W </li>\n<li>Minimum Input: 200W RMS </li>\n', ''),
(642, 1, 'Vibe Space 12 3000W 12" Subwoofer', '<newtab>\n<tabname><center>Description</center></tabname>\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc"><p>The SPACE SPL subwoofer is a class above the competition for reliability, quality and SPL. </p><br>\n<p>Extreme bass, cutting edge design, superior style and severe power, the Space SPL takes subwoofer parameters and specifications to another level. Incorporating the very latest in cutting edge technology, Mechanical Thermal Unity, developed to enhance subwoofer cooling, the subs operate at much higher temperatures with less distortion and stress. </p><br>\n<p>Heat is dissipated directly through the front of the lightweight alloy super rigid cone which is seamlessly attached to flanged dual high temperature alloy voice coils and set in dual layer foam surrounds, which means massive power and serious cone excursion. Admiration guaranteed.\n</p>\n</div>\n</tabtext>\n</newtab>\n\n<newtab>\n<tabname><center>Features</center></tabname>\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc"><ul><li>Size: 12" (323mm) </li>\n<li>RMS Input: 1000 W </li>\n<li>Peak Output: 3000 W </li>\n<li>Sensitivity: 86dB </li>\n<li>Frequency Response: 20-500 Hz </li>\n<li>Impedance: Dual 4ohm </li>\n<li>Mounting Depth: 175mm </li>\n<li>Mounting Diameter: 285mm </li>\n<li>Recommended Amp: BlackBox IV </li>\n<li>Recommended Enclosure Volume: 2.5 CuFt</li></ul>\n</div>\n</tabtext>\n</newtab>\n\n<newtab>\n<tabname><center>Support</center></tabname>\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc"><a href="http://www.vibeaudio.co.uk/support/tsparameters/sub-space12d4.pdf" target="_blank"><img src="images/icons/pdf.png" align="left" style="vertical-align:middle"/>Instruction Manual</a><br>\n</div>\n</tabtext>\n</newtab>\n\n<newtab>\n<tabname><center>More Images</center></tabname>\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc"><p></p>\n</div>\n</tabtext>\n</newtab>', 'www.vibeaudio.co.uk/products/spacesub12/', NULL, '', 52, '<br>\n<li>Size: 12" (323mm) </li>\n<li>RMS Input: 1000 W </li>\n<li>Peak Output: 3000 W </li>\n<li>Sensitivity: 86dB </li>\n', ''),
(643, 1, 'Vibe Space 15 3600W 15" Subwoofer', '<newtab>\n<tabname><center>Description</center></tabname>\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc"><p>The VIBE R&D masters proudly present the SPACE range of Performance SPL subwoofers. We use the term sound pressure level (SPL) lightly, because the SPACE woofer is as much a reference sub as it is an SPL sub - yet it still sits a class above most SPL subwoofers. We have achieved what most SPL subwoofers fail through continuous engineering combined with new technologies and materials  this has enabled us to create an immaculate subwoofer  producing reference sound quality at huge sound pressure levels.</p><br>\n<p>Making a subwoofer that can produce SPL levels of both tight bass and deep bass to a good musical level is near impossible  VIBE R&D have been researching this success for many years  we believe we have surpassed on our own goals and now offer it to you in the form of the SPACE subwoofer.</p><br>\n<p>To summate; the SPACE has the dexterity of a light footed 8" sub and the power of a heavyweight competition SPL spec sub. This is undoubtedly the VIBE teams favourite product for all the reasons you are reading here. Perfection in low frequency reproduction.\n</p>\n</div>\n</tabtext>\n</newtab>\n\n<newtab>\n<tabname><center>Features</center></tabname>\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc"><ul><li>Speaker Size: 15" (392mm) </li>\n<li>RMS Power: 1200w </li>\n<li>Peak Power: 3600w </li>\n<li>Sensitivity: 90dB </li>\n<li>Frequency Response: 18 - 500Khz </li>\n<li>Impedance: Dual 2 or 4ohm </li>\n<li>Mounting Depth: 200mm </li>\n<li>Mounting Diameter: 355mm </li>\n<li>Recommended Vol: 3.0Cu.Ft. </li>\n<li>Recommended Amp: SLICK a7 </li>\n<li>BlackBOX BASS 4 </li>\n<li>BlackBOX BASS 5 </li></ul>\n</div>\n</tabtext>\n</newtab>\n\n<newtab>\n<tabname><center>Support</center></tabname>\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc"><a href="http://www.vibeaudio.co.uk/support/tsparameters/sub-space15d4.pdf" target="_blank"><img src="images/icons/pdf.png" align="left" style="vertical-align:middle"/>Instruction Manual</a><br>\n</div>\n</tabtext>\n</newtab>\n\n<newtab>\n<tabname><center>More Images</center></tabname>\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc"><p></p>\n</div>\n</tabtext>\n</newtab>', 'www.vibeaudio.co.uk/products/spacesub15/', NULL, '', 55, '<br>\n<li>Speaker Size: 15" (392mm) </li>\n<li>RMS Power: 1200w </li>\n<li>Peak Power: 3600w </li>\n<li>Sensitivity: 90dB </li>\n', ''),
(644, 1, 'Vibe BlackDeath BD151C 15" 7500W Subwoofer', '<newtab>\n<tabname><center>Description</center></tabname>\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc"><p>Vibe BlackDeath BD151C. A new SPL heavyweight has entered the ring. Weighing in at a mighty 22kg, the all new VIBE BLACKDEATH 15 inch competition SPL subwoofer is spreading fear amongst its worthy opponents, its edge is masterful engineering in the true sense of professional competition subwoofer design, its mission is to be champion of the SPL lanes.</p><br>\n<p>Every detail of the BLACKDEATH BD151C subwoofer has been taken to extreme levels never before seen in the world of car audio. Ludicrous excursion and unfathomable power handling combine to create deadly bass.</p><br>\n<p></p>\n</div>\n</tabtext>\n</newtab>\n\n<newtab>\n<tabname><center>Features</center></tabname>\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc"><ul><li>Type: Competition SPL Subwoofer </li>\n<li>Speaker Size: 15" (392mm) </li>\n<li>RMS Power: 2500w </li>\n<li>Peak Power: 7500w </li>\n<li>Sensitivity: 94.3dB </li>\n<li>Frequency Response: 15Hz - 850KHz </li>\n<li>Impedance: Dual 1ohm </li>\n<li>Mounting Depth: 212mm </li>\n<li>Mounting Diameter: 350mm </li>\n<li>Voice Coil 3 inch 4 Layer </li>\n<li>Recommended Vol. 4.5Cu.Ft. </li>\n<li>Recommended Amplifier Blackbox Bass 5 </li></ul>\n</p>\n</div>\n</tabtext>\n</newtab>\n\n<newtab>\n<tabname><center>Support</center></tabname>\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc"><a href="http://www.vibeaudio.co.uk/support/tsparameters/sub-blackdeath15.pdf" target="_blank"><img src="images/icons/pdf.png" align="left" style="vertical-align:middle"/>Instruction Manual</a><br>\n</div>\n</tabtext>\n</newtab>\n\n<newtab>\n<tabname><center>More Images</center></tabname>\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc"><p></p>\n</div>\n</tabtext>\n</newtab>', 'www.vibeaudio.co.uk/products/blackdeath15c/', NULL, '', 73, '<br>\n<li>Type: Competition SPL Subwoofer </li>\n<li>Speaker Size: 15" (392mm) </li>\n<li>RMS Power: 2500w </li>\n<li>Peak Power: 7500w </li>\n', ''),
(645, 1, 'Vibe BlackDeath BD154P 15" 7500W Subwoofer', '<newtab>\n<tabname><center>Description</center></tabname>\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc"><p>Vibe Blackdeath BD154P. A new SPL heavyweight has entered the ring. Weighing in at a mighty 22kg, the all new VIBE BLACKDEATH 15 inch competition SPL subwoofer is spreading fear amongst its worthy opponents, its edge is masterful engineering in the true sense of professional competition subwoofer design, its mission is to be champion of the SPL lanes.</p><br>\n<p>Every detail of the BLACKDEATH subwoofer has been taken to extreme levels never before seen in the world of car audio. Ludicrous excursion and unfathomable power handling combine to create deadly bass.</p>\n</div>\n</tabtext>\n</newtab>\n\n<newtab>\n<tabname><center>Features</center></tabname>\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc"><ul><li>Type: Competition SPL Subwoofer </li>\n<li>Speaker Size: 15" (392mm) </li>\n<li>RMS Power: 2500w </li>\n<li>Peak Power: 7500w </li>\n<li>Sensitivity: 93dB </li>\n<li>Frequency Response: 15 - 850,000Hz </li>\n<li>Impedance: Dual 4ohm </li>\n<li>Mounting Depth: 212mm </li>\n<li>Mounting Diameter: 350mm </li>\n<li>Voice Coil 3 inch 4 layer </li>\n<li>Recommended Vol. 4.5Cu.Ft. </li>\n<li>Recommended Amplifier Blackbox Bass 5</li></ul>\n</div>\n</tabtext>\n</newtab>\n\n<newtab>\n<tabname><center>Support</center></tabname>\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc"><a href="http://www.vibeaudio.co.uk/support/tsparameters/sub-blackdeath15p.pdf" target="_blank"><img src="images/icons/pdf.png" align="left" style="vertical-align:middle"/>Instruction Manual</a><br>\n</div>\n</tabtext>\n</newtab>\n\n<newtab>\n<tabname><center>More Images</center></tabname>\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc"><p></p>\n</div>\n</tabtext>\n</newtab>', 'www.vibeaudio.co.uk/products/blackdeath15p/', NULL, '', 73, '<br>\n<li>Type: Competition SPL Subwoofer </li>\n<li>Speaker Size: 15" (392mm) </li>\n<li>RMS Power: 2500w </li>\n<li>Peak Power: 7500w </li>\n', ''),
(646, 1, 'Vibe Slick A0 400W 2/1 Channel Amplifier', '<newtab>\n<tabname><center>Description</center></tabname>\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc"><p>VIBE are pleased to present the SLICK range of amplifiers. This range has the newly developed VIBE Slick Heatsink. The sink is super smooth and has elegant profiling and a rubberised finish. End caps terminate the profile whilst hiding wiring and connections.</p><br>\n<p>The amplifiers are VIBEs entry level range offering big performance for a more affordable price.\n</p>\n</div>\n</tabtext>\n</newtab>\n\n<newtab>\n<tabname><center>Features</center></tabname>\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc"><ul><li>Power Bridged 1 x 200 WRMS</li>\n<li>2/1 channel amplifier</li>\n<li>Super Slick design with rubberised finish</li>\n<li>Twin end caps for stealth connections</li>\n<li>Soft turn on feature</li>\n<li>Optional bass boost remote control</li>\n<li>0-12db bass boost</li>\n<li>2 ohm stable</li>\n<li>Adjustable HP/LP/Flat crossovers</li>\n<li>High quality surface mounted components</li>\n<li>Double sided PCB</li>\n<li>Preouts for linking additional amplifiers</li>\n<li>Lo-level and Hi-level inputs</li>\n<li>Built in relay protection</li>\n<li>Max Power 400W</li>\n<li>Power @ 4 ohms 2x 75 WRMS</li>\n<li>Power @ 2 Ohms 2 x 100 WRMS</li>\n<li>Minimum speaker impedance 2 ohm (stereo)</li>\n<li>THD Distortion 0.14 %</li>\n<li>Input Sensitivity 200 mv - 6V</li>\n<li>Signal to Noise Ratio 93 dB</li>\n<li>Size H 65mm x W 380mm x D 245mm</li></ul>\n</div>\n</tabtext>\n</newtab>\n\n<newtab>\n<tabname><center>Support</center></tabname>\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc"><p></p>\n</div>\n</tabtext>\n</newtab>\n\n<newtab>\n<tabname><center>More Images</center></tabname>\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc"><p></p>\n</div>\n</tabtext>\n</newtab>', 'www.vibeaudio.co.uk/products/slicka0/', NULL, '', 60, '<br>\n<li>Max Power 400W</li>\n<li>Power @ 4 ohms 2x 75 WRMS</li>\n<li>Power @ 2 Ohms 2 x 100 WRMS</li>\n<li>Minimum speaker impedance 2 ohm (stereo)</li>\n', ''),
(647, 1, 'Vibe Slick A1 800W 4 / 3 / 2 Channel Amplifier', '<newtab>\n<tabname><center>Description</center></tabname>\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc"><p>VIBE are pleased to present the SLICK range of amplifiers. This range has the newly developed VIBE Slick Heatsink. The sink is super smooth and has elegant profiling and a rubberised finish. End caps terminate the profile whilst hiding wiring and connections.</p><br>\n<p>The amplifiers are VIBEs entry level range offering big performance for a more affordable price.\n</p>\n</div>\n</tabtext>\n</newtab>\n\n<newtab>\n<tabname><center>Features</center></tabname>\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc"><ul><li>4/3/2 channel amplifier</li>\n<li>Super Slick design with rubberised finish</li>\n<li>Twin end caps for stealth connections</li>\n<li>Soft turn on feature</li>\n<li>Optional bass boost remote control</li>\n<li>0-12db bass boost</li>\n<li>2 ohm stable</li>\n<li>Adjustable HP/LP/Flat crossovers</li>\n<li>High quality surface mounted components</li>\n<li>Double sided PCB</li>\n<li>Lo-level and Hi-level inputs</li>\n<li>Built in relay protection</li>\n<li>Max Power 800W</li>\n<li>Power @ 4 ohms 4x 75 WRMS</li>\n<li>Power @ 2 Ohms 4 x 100 WRMS</li>\n<li>Power Bridged 2 x 200 WRMS</li>\n<li>Minimum speaker impedance 2 ohm (stereo)</li>\n<li>THD Distortion 0.14 %</li>\n<li>Input Sensitivity 200 mv - 6V</li>\n<li>Signal to Noise Ratio 92 dB</li>\n<li>Size H 65mm x W 430mm x D 245mm</li></ul>\n</div>\n</tabtext>\n</newtab>\n\n<newtab>\n<tabname><center>Support</center></tabname>\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc"><p></p>\n</div>\n</tabtext>\n</newtab>\n\n<newtab>\n<tabname><center>More Images</center></tabname>\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc"><p></p>\n</div>\n</tabtext>\n</newtab>', 'www.vibeaudio.co.uk/products/slicka1/', NULL, '', 51, '<br>\n<li>Max Power 800W</li>\n<li>Power @ 4 ohms 4x 75 WRMS</li>\n<li>Power @ 2 Ohms 4 x 100 WRMS</li>\n<li>Power Bridged 2 x 200 WRMS</li>\n', ''),
(648, 1, 'Vibe Slick A7 1330W Mono Channel Amplifier', '<newtab>\n<tabname><center>Description</center></tabname>\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc"><p>VIBE are pleased to present the SLICK range of amplifiers. This range has the newly developed VIBE Slick Heatsink. The sink is super smooth and has elegant profiling and a rubberised finish. End caps terminate the profile whilst hiding wiring and connections. </p><br>\n<p>The amplifiers are VIBEs entry level range offering big performance for a more affordable price. </p><br>\n<p></p>\n</div>\n</tabtext>\n</newtab>\n\n<newtab>\n<tabname><center>Features</center></tabname>\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc"><ul><li>Power @ 4 ohms 1 x 300 WRMS </li>\n<li>Power @ 2 Ohms 1 x 600 WRMS </li>\n<li>Power @ 1 Ohm 1 x 750 WRMS </li>\n<li>Max Power: 1300W </li>\n<li>Class D  digital monoblock amplifier </li>\n<li>Super Slick design with rubberised finish </li>\n<li>Twin end caps for stealth connections </li>\n<li>Class D  digital monoblock amplifier </li>\n<li>Super Slick design with rubberised finish </li>\n<li>Twin end caps for stealth connections </li>\n<li>Soft turn on feature </li>\n<li>In dash bass boost remote control </li>\n<li>0  180 phase control </li>\n<li>18db bass boost </li>\n<li>Fully adjustable Subsonic filter </li>\n<li>1 ohm stable </li>\n<li>Selectable 12/24db crossovers </li>\n<li>High quality surface mounted components </li>\n<li>Double sided PCB </li>\n<li>Preouts for linking additional amplifiers </li>\n<li>Lo-level and Hi-level inputs </li>\n<li>Built in relay protection </li>\n<li>Power @ 4 ohms 1 x 300 WRMS </li>\n<li>Power @ 2 Ohms 1 x 600 WRMS </li>\n<li>Power @ 1 Ohm 1 x 750 WRMS </li>\n<li>Max Power: 1300W </li>\n<li>Minimum speaker impedance 1 ohm </li>\n<li>THD Distortion 0.1 % </li>\n<li>IMD Distortion 0.1 % </li>\n<li>Input Sensitivity 200 mv - 6V </li>\n<li>Input Impedance 15 K </li>\n<li>Signal to Noise Ratio 85 dB </li>\n<li>Remote Bass Control 0 dB -+12 dB </li>\n<li>Low Pass Filter 35 Hz - 250 Hz </li>\n<li>Bass Boost 0 dB -+24 dB </li>\n<li>Subsonic Filter 16 Hz - 80 Hz </li>\n<li>Size H65 mm xW 425 mm x D247 mm</li></ul>\n</div>\n</tabtext>\n</newtab>\n\n<newtab>\n<tabname><center>Support</center></tabname>\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc"><a href="http://www.vibeaudio.co.uk/support/manuals/manual_slicka7.pdf" target="_blank"><img src="images/icons/pdf.png" align="left" style="vertical-align:middle"/>Instruction Manual</a><br>\n</div>\n</tabtext>\n</newtab>\n\n<newtab>\n<tabname><center>More Images</center></tabname>\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc"><p></p>\n</div>\n</tabtext>\n</newtab>', 'www.vibeaudio.co.uk/products/slicka7/', NULL, '', 123, '<br>\n<li>Power @ 4 ohms 1 x 300 WRMS </li>\n<li>Power @ 2 Ohms 1 x 600 WRMS </li>\n<li>Power @ 1 Ohm 1 x 750 WRMS </li>\n<li>Max Power: 1300W </li>\n', ''),
(649, 1, 'Vibe BlackBox Stereo 2 700W 2 Channel Amplifier', '<newtab>\r\n<tabname><center>Description</center></tabname>\r\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc"><p>The BlackBox Stereo class AB amps are highly versatile and fully adaptable to multiple speaker configurations. The newest Internal Convection Cooling ICC vented technology is incorporated to eliminate the need for external cooling fins so enhancing the contemporary aesthetics of the amp whilst keeping things cool. Compact and powerful, the amps offer unparalleled audio performance and quality electronic components which produce clean, controllable, dynamic audiophile sound. </p>\r\n</div>\r\n</tabtext>\r\n</newtab>\r\n\r\n<newtab>\r\n<tabname><center>Features</center></tabname>\r\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc"><ul><li>Max Power: 700 w </li>\r\n<li>RMS Out @4ohm stereo: 2 x 110 w </li>\r\n<li>RMS Out @2ohm stereo: 2 x 175 w </li>\r\n<li>RMS Out @4ohm bridged: 1 x 350 w </li>\r\n<li>Signal To Noise Ratio: 114 dB </li>\r\n<li>Frequency Response: 20 - 20,000 Hz </li>\r\n<li>Total Harmonic Distortion: 0.02% </li>\r\n<li>Crosover Type: LP/HP/Flat </li>\r\n<li>Crossover Range: 55 - 5,500 Hz </li>\r\n<li>Crpossover Slope: 24dB </li>\r\n<li>Bass Enhance: 15dB </li>\r\n<li>Height: 57 mm </li>\r\n<li>Width: 357 mm </li>\r\n<li>Depth: 224 mm</li></ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</tabtext>\r\n</newtab>\r\n\r\n<newtab>\r\n<tabname><center>Support</center></tabname>\r\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc"><a href="http://www.vibeaudio.co.uk/support/manuals/manual_sterio2and4.pdf" target="_blank"><img src="images/icons/pdf.png" align="left" style="vertical-align:middle"/>Instruction Manual</a><br>\r\n</div>\r\n</tabtext>\r\n</newtab>\r\n\r\n<newtab>\r\n<tabname><center>More Images</center></tabname>\r\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc"><p></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</tabtext>\r\n</newtab>', 'www.vibeaudio.co.uk/products/blackboxs2/', NULL, '', 378, '<br>\r\n<li>Max Power: 700 w </li>\r\n<li>RMS Out @4ohm stereo: 2 x 110 w </li>\r\n<li>RMS Out @2ohm stereo: 2 x 175 w </li>\r\n<li>RMS Out @4ohm bridged: 1 x 350 w </li>', ''),
(650, 1, 'Vibe BlackBox S4 1400W 4 / 3 / 2 Channel Amplifier', '<newtab>\r\n<tabname><center>Description</center></tabname>\r\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc"><p>VIBEs all new range of BlackBox STEREO amplifiers are at the cutting edge of amplifier design and technology; these class AB amps are highly versatile and fully adaptable to multiple speaker configurations. The newest Internal Convection Cooling ICC vented technology is incorporated to eliminate the need for external cooling fins so enhancing the contemporary aesthetics of the amp whilst keeping things cool. Compact and powerful, the amps offer unparalleled audio performance and quality electronic components which produce clean, controllable, dynamic audiophile sound.</p><br>\r\n<p>The four layer circuit board, on board active low and high pass filters with frequency multiplier, BassEnhance delivering 18dB of boost at 45Hz are common features of the BlackBox STEREO amplifiers. Built in microprocessor circuits actively monitor the amplifier operation, the BlackBox literally looks after both itself and its connecting speakers.</p><br>\r\n<p>Another first for VIBE is the variable input sensitivity, gain matching is very important in car audio systems and it is for this reason that VIBE have added 3 different input sensitivity ranges to the new Stereo amplifiers, so whether you have 0.2v  0.6v, 0.6v  2v or a mighty 2v - 8v the amplifiers deliver maximum results with unrivalled signal to noise ratio.</p><br>\r\n<p>The new range of BlackBox STEREO amplifiers are the best sounding amplifiers ever produced by VIBE. Featuring a completely new circuit and improved power supply which has given huge gains in power delivery and headroom which you can really hear on busy sections of music where the sound from lesser amplifiers crumbles into distortion - the BlackBox STEREO amplifiers deliver the music with grace, poise and finesse, just as the artist intended.\r\n</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</tabtext>\r\n</newtab>\r\n\r\n<newtab>\r\n<tabname><center>Features</center></tabname>\r\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc"><p><b>Features:</b></p><br>\r\n<ul><li>Audiophile sound quality</li>\r\n<li>Stereo, bridged or tri-mode operation for maximum flexibility</li>\r\n<li>ICC Internal Convention Cooling</li>\r\n<li>Advanced 4 Layer circuit board</li>\r\n<li>Microprocessor circuit monitors amplifier operation</li>\r\n<li>24 db per octave High pass and low pass crossovers</li>\r\n<li>Crossover range 55Hz  3,000Hz</li>\r\n<li>Frequency multiplier eliminates the need for an external active crossover</li>\r\n<li>Selectable input sensitivity 0.2v  0.6v, 0.6v  2v and 2v - 8v</li>\r\n<li>Excellent signal to noise ratio of 114dB</li>\r\n<li>Total harmonic distortion as low as 0.02%</li>\r\n<li>End caps with illuminated BlackBox logo indicates amplifier status</li>\r\n<li>Optional remote level control BBR1</li></ul>\r\n<p><b>Specifications:</b></p><br>\r\n<ul><li>Type: 4 / 3 / 2 Channel</li>\r\n<li>Class: AB</li>\r\n<li>Height: 57mm</li>\r\n<li>Width: 479mm</li>\r\n<li>Depth: 224mm</li>\r\n<li>Max power: 1400w</li>\r\n<li>RMS @ 4 Ohm stereo: 4 x 110w</li>\r\n<li>RMS @ 2 Ohm Stereo: 4 x 175w</li>\r\n<li>RMS @ 4 Ohm Bridged: 2 x 350w</li>\r\n<li>SNR: 110 db</li>\r\n<li>Frequency Response: 10-50Khz</li>\r\n<li>THD: 0.03%</li>\r\n<li>Bass Boost: 0 - 15db</li>\r\n<li>HPF: 55hz - 5.5Khz</li>\r\n<li>LPF: 55hz - 5.5Khz</li>\r\n<li>Input mode: 2 or 4 Channel</li>\r\n<li>Low level input: 0.2 - 8v</li>\r\n<li>High level input: 0.4 - 15v</li></ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</tabtext>\r\n</newtab>\r\n\r\n<newtab>\r\n<tabname><center>Support</center></tabname>\r\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc"><a href="http://www.vibeaudio.co.uk/support/manuals/manual_sterio2and4.pdf" target="_blank"><img src="images/icons/pdf.png" align="left" style="vertical-align:middle"/>Instruction Manual</a><br>\r\n</div>\r\n</tabtext>\r\n</newtab>\r\n\r\n<newtab>\r\n<tabname><center>More Images</center></tabname>\r\n<tabtext><div id="prodDesc"><p></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</tabtext>\r\n</newtab>', 'www.vibeaudio.co.uk/products/blackboxs4/', NULL, '', 437, '<br>\r\n<li>Max power: 1400w</li>\r\n<li>RMS @ 4 Ohm stereo: 4 x 110w</li>\r\n<li>RMS @ 2 Ohm Stereo: 4 x 175w</li>\r\n<li>RMS @ 4 Ohm Bridged: 2 x 350w</li>', ''),
